    <entry>
        <title type="html"><![CDATA[Getting started with Earthball]]></title>
        <id>https://earthball.dev/getting-started/</id>
        <link href="https://earthball.dev/getting-started/"/>
        <updated>2021-02-06T01:19:13.088Z</updated>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Create a new Earthball site with the <code>earthball new</code> command.</p>
<p>Earthball depends on recent node versions (it's developed with node 15), so first make sure you've got node installed.</p>
<p>You might use <a href="https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm">nvm</a> to install multiple node versions.</p>
<p>After you've got node installed, create a directory for your new site:</p>
<pre><code class="hljs language-shell">mkdir cool-new-site</code></pre>
<p>And move into that directory:</p>
<pre><code class="hljs language-shell">cd cool-new-site</code></pre>
<p>Next run <code>npm init</code> and install earthball with npm:</p>
<pre><code class="hljs language-shell">npm init
npm install earthball --dev</code></pre>
<p>Finally, create the site with <code>earthball new</code>, which takes <code>title</code> and <code>description</code> arguments:</p>
<pre><code class="hljs language-shell">earthball new --title "cool site" --description "cool earthball site"</code></pre>
]]></content>
